nunn library NEWS -- history of user-visible changes.
Author - Antonino Calderone - <acaldmail@gmail.com> - (c) 2015, 2016

Please send nunn bug reports to <acaldmail@gmail.com>.

Jun 25, 2026
* Released nunn library 2.1
- Add a GoogleTest unit-test suite (fetched via CMake FetchContent, registered
  with CTest) covering Vector, cost functions, Perceptron, MlpNN, QMatrix, the
  policies and the QLearn/SARSA learners
- Fix Vector(const double*, size_t): it copied v_len bytes instead of v_len
  doubles, dropping most of the data
- Fix SoftmaxPolicy: avoid dereferencing the end iterator on rounding, guard
  against a zero/negative temperature, and honour the RndGen template parameter
- Fix EGreedyPolicy: clamp the random action index so it can never run past the
  end of the valid-action list
- Fix Sarsa::learn(): the move counter was incremented twice per step
- Fix NNTrainer::runTraining(): the sample index is now advanced even without a
  progress callback, so partial-set training (p2use < 1.0) stops correctly
- Fix QLearn::updateQ(): guard against states with no valid actions
- Make MlpNN/Perceptron save() lossless by writing doubles at full precision
- Minor cleanups: remove unused Policy members, const-correct trainer iterator
  comparisons, default/movable QMatrix special members
- Examples build fixes: titanic now includes <numeric>; the mnist helper library
  exports its symbols on Windows
- Note: the EGreedy/Softmax zero-Q exploration heuristic and the hidden-layer
  bias term in backprop are intentionally left unchanged and deferred to 3.0

Mar 22, 2019
- Change license to MIT
- Switch to cmake for compiling (remove autotool support)

